| 3.7 | No information conveyed by colour alone | Shapes + labels distinguish all elements |
| 3.8 | No copyrighted or external images | Source script generates all graphics procedurally |
| 3.9 | Alt text provided in README for each figure | ≥2 sentences per figure |

## Cross-Cutting

| # | Criterion | Verification |
|---|-----------|--------------|
| C.1 | Manifest exists at `tools/manifest.txt` | `sha256sum -c tools/manifest.txt` all OK |
| C.2 | Generator script is self-contained | `python3 paper/figures/gen_diagrams.py` with only matplotlib |
| C.3 | No files published or pushed to any remote | Local-only; user runs push commands manually |
| C.4 | Naming consistency across all files | All use: IDLE, EVAL, SELECT, EXEC, POST, HARDSTOP, LSPS, HardstopRecoverThm, HardstopToIdle |

---

## Verification Commands

```bash
# Run all checks in sequence:
cd mfcs

# 1. Checksum verification
sha256sum -c tools/manifest.txt

# 2. File presence
ls -la paper/figures/fig1_state_ring.{svg,pdf} \
       paper/figures/fig2_latch_flow.{svg,pdf} \
       paper/figures/fig3_hardstop_recovery.{svg,pdf} \
       paper/figures/diagram_sheet.{svg,pdf} \
       paper/figures/gen_diagrams.py \
       docs/README.md \
       tools/manifest.txt

# 3. Canonical name consistency (SVG sources)
for name in IDLE EVAL SELECT EXEC POST HARDSTOP LSPS HardstopRecoverThm HardstopToIdle; do
  echo -n "$name: "
  grep -rl "$name" paper/figures/*.svg docs/README.md | wc -l
done

# 4. Regeneration test
python3 paper/figures/gen_diagrams.py
sha256sum -c tools/manifest.txt
```
